node.text:
this experience changed me much more than i thought it would. definitely taught me that i really don’t appreciate the life i have as much as i should. everything, literally everything, could be taken away from you in a second.
•
for a trip i was waiting more than 5 years for, Chernobyl did not disappoint. i hope the words of grandma Marusa stuck with you as hard as they did for me

node.text:
5 years of exploring, waiting for this moment. when we first began Chernobyl was at the top of every list and at the beginning of 25x25 i said we 100% need to explore chernobyl.
•
this documentary is different. and being one of the most significant places in recent history, this story is bigger than youtube. and it impacted me more than i thought it would. part 1 out now ♥️

node.text: this night felt like a dream… after 5 days of constant filming and energy drinks we pushed for the more eerie investigation of them all. energy peaked as we all turned into Call Of Duty Special Ops Agents and moved throughout a pitch black building to scare a bunch of high school kids… ah what a memory
